# Deliberate dev-environment cost/scope trade-offs, mirroring the checkov
# soft-fail rationale (#111). Trivy is BLOCKING in all three gate layers
# (pre-commit / make security / CI) — new findings fail; accepted ones are
# ignored here explicitly with a reason. Revisit when productionizing (#150).

# Security group rules allow unrestricted egress (0.0.0.0/0) — standard dev
# posture; egress restriction is a production-hardening task.
AVD-AWS-0104

# S3 buckets use SSE-S3, not customer-managed KMS keys — CMK adds cost and
# key-management overhead not justified for this dev stack.
AVD-AWS-0132

# ALB listener is HTTP: TLS terminates at CloudFront; no custom domain/ACM
# cert on the ALB yet (see #79 for the CloudFront security-header work).
AVD-AWS-0054

# ALB is public by design: CloudFront -> public ALB origin architecture.
AVD-AWS-0053

# drop_invalid_header_fields not enabled on the ALB — cheap to fix; candidate
# for removal from this list when the ALB config is next touched.
AVD-AWS-0052

# No WAF on the CloudFront distribution — cost/scope decision for dev.
AVD-AWS-0011

# Alerts SNS topic (#42) uses the AWS-managed key (alias/aws/sns), not a
# customer-managed KMS key — CMK adds cost/key-management overhead not
# justified for alarm notification text on this dev stack (same rationale as
# AVD-AWS-0132 for S3).
AVD-AWS-0136
